# Aero Templates

Document discoveries from code exploration in [_reference/DISCOVERY.md](_reference/DISCOVERY.md).

Full script taxonomy: [docs/script-taxonomy.md](docs/script-taxonomy.md). Legacy `on:build` / `on:client` were replaced by `is:build` and plain `<script>` (client).

## TDD (red-to-green)

When implementing new features or tracking down bugs, use TDD: (1) write or run a failing test that captures the behavior or reproduces the bug (red); (2) implement the minimal change to make the test pass (green); (3) refactor if needed. For bugs, always add or adjust a failing test first; do not skip to the fix.

## Component Naming

Use `-component` or `-layout` suffix in markup; import without suffix (resolves to .html):

```html
<script is:build>
	import header from '@components/header'
</script>
<header-component title="Hello" />
```

## Script Types

- `<script is:build>` â€” Build time; one per file; has `Aero.props`, `Aero.site`, `site`, imports. Add `lang="ts"` for IntelliSense/formatting when using TypeScript.
- Plain `<script>` (no `is:*`) â€” Client module; Vite bundles as a virtual module. Use `props` / `data-props` to pass values into the module.
- `<script is:inline>` â€” Left in the DOM where written; not bundled by Vite; runs as classic inline script in the browser.
- `<script is:blocking>` â€” Emitted in `<head>` to run before the rest of the page.
- `<script src="...">` â€” External or resolved local scripts per [docs/script-taxonomy.md](docs/script-taxonomy.md).

Use one of these for **executable** script bodies: `is:build`, plain `<script>` (client module), `is:inline`, or `is:blocking`. Do not use deprecated `on:build` / `on:client`.

## Props

- Pass: attributes, `props` / `data-props` (including spreads), as in [docs/interpolation.md](docs/interpolation.md).
- Receive: destructure `Aero.props` in `<script is:build>`.

```html
<my-component title="{ site.title }" />
<my-component props="{ componentProps }" />
<my-component props="{ ...spreadProps }" />
<my-component props />
<script is:build>
	const { title } = Aero.props
</script>
```

## Loops and Slots

- Loops: `(data-)for="{ const item of items }"` then `{ item.name }` etc.
- Slots: use both `name` and `slot` attributes on `<slot>` elements

## Client Stack

- Alpine.js: `x-data`, `x-model`, `:disabled` etc. are preserved (not interpolated)
- HTMX: `hx-post`, `hx-target` etc. passed through
- Alpine attrs match `^(x-|[@:.]).*` and skip `{ }` interpolation
